{
  "info": {
    "name": "Geniova Drive API",
    "description": "API para gestión de ficheros en NAS Synology.\n\nAutenticación: JWT via header `Authorization: Bearer <token>` o cookie `auth_token`.\n\nPermisos UNIX: r (read), w (write), x (execute/navigate), d (delete).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:3000",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{token}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/health",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "health"]
            },
            "description": "Devuelve el estado de la aplicación y la conexión a la base de datos.\n\nNo requiere autenticación."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200 or 503', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 503]);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has expected structure', function () {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(body).to.have.property('status');",
                  "  pm.expect(body).to.have.property('timestamp');",
                  "  pm.expect(body).to.have.property('services');",
                  "  pm.expect(body.services).to.have.property('app');",
                  "  pm.expect(body.services).to.have.property('database');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Files - Listing",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Directory",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/files?path=/datosnas&page=1&limit=50",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "files"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "path",
                  "value": "/datosnas",
                  "description": "Virtual path del directorio a listar"
                },
                {
                  "key": "page",
                  "value": "1",
                  "description": "Página (default: 1)"
                },
                {
                  "key": "limit",
                  "value": "50",
                  "description": "Items por página (default: 50, max: 200)"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Lista el contenido de un directorio con metadatos.\n\nRequiere permiso `r` (read) en el path.\n\nOrdena: carpetas primero, luego ficheros, ambos alfabéticamente.\n\nFiltra automáticamente carpetas de sistema Synology (#recycle, @eaDir)."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has pagination structure', function () {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(body).to.have.property('path');",
                  "  pm.expect(body).to.have.property('items');",
                  "  pm.expect(body).to.have.property('total');",
                  "  pm.expect(body).to.have.property('page');",
                  "  pm.expect(body).to.have.property('limit');",
                  "  pm.expect(body).to.have.property('pages');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Items have expected fields', function () {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (body.items.length > 0) {",
                  "    const item = body.items[0];",
                  "    pm.expect(item).to.have.property('name');",
                  "    pm.expect(item).to.have.property('type');",
                  "    pm.expect(item).to.have.property('size');",
                  "    pm.expect(item).to.have.property('modified');",
                  "    pm.expect(item).to.have.property('path');",
                  "    pm.expect(item.type).to.be.oneOf(['file', 'directory']);",
                  "  }",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "List Directory - No Path (400)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/files",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "files"]
            },
            "description": "Debe devolver 400 si no se proporciona el parámetro path."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 400', function () {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(400);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Error message mentions path', function () {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(body.error).to.include('path');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "List Subdirectory",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/files?path=/datosnas/stls&page=1&limit=20",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "files"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "path",
                  "value": "/datosnas/stls"
                },
                {
                  "key": "page",
                  "value": "1"
                },
                {
                  "key": "limit",
                  "value": "20"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Listar una subcarpeta específica."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200 or 404', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 404]);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Files - Search",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Search Files",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/files/search?path=/datosnas&q=model",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "files", "search"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "path",
                  "value": "/datosnas",
                  "description": "Directorio raíz donde buscar"
                },
                {
                  "key": "q",
                  "value": "model",
                  "description": "Término de búsqueda (mín 2 caracteres)"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Busca ficheros/carpetas por nombre de forma recursiva.\n\nBúsqueda case-insensitive. Máximo 100 resultados.\n\nRequiere permiso `r` (read) en el path raíz."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200 or error', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 400, 403]);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  pm.test('Response has search structure', function () {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(body).to.have.property('query');",
                  "    pm.expect(body).to.have.property('results');",
                  "    pm.expect(body).to.have.property('total');",
                  "    pm.expect(body.results).to.be.an('array');",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Search - Query Too Short (400)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/files/search?path=/datosnas&q=a",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "files", "search"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "path",
                  "value": "/datosnas"
                },
                {
                  "key": "q",
                  "value": "a"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Búsqueda con query de 1 carácter. Debe devolver 400."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Short query returns 400', function () {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(400);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Files - Operations",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create Directory",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"path\": \"/datosnas/test-folder\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/files/mkdir",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "files", "mkdir"]
            },
            "description": "Crea un nuevo directorio.\n\nRequiere permiso `w` (write) en el directorio padre.\n\nDevuelve 201 si se crea correctamente, 409 si ya existe."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 201 or 409', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([201, 409]);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has path', function () {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    pm.expect(body).to.have.property('path');",
                  "  }",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Rename Item",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"path\": \"/datosnas/test-folder\",\n  \"newName\": \"test-folder-renamed\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/files/rename",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "files", "rename"]
            },
            "description": "Renombra un fichero o carpeta.\n\nRequiere permiso `w` (write) en el directorio padre.\n\n`newName` debe ser solo el nombre, sin separadores de ruta."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200 or error', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 400, 403, 404, 409]);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Success response has path', function () {",
                  "  if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(body).to.have.property('path');",
                  "  }",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Move Item",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"source\": \"/datosnas/test-folder-renamed\",\n  \"destination\": \"/datosnas\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/files/move",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "files", "move"]
            },
            "description": "Mueve un fichero o carpeta a otro directorio.\n\nRequiere permiso `w` (write) tanto en el directorio origen como en el destino.\n\nEl destino debe ser un directorio existente."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200 or error', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 400, 403, 404, 409]);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Success response has path', function () {",
                  "  if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(body).to.have.property('path');",
                  "  }",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete Item",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/files?path=/datosnas/test-folder-renamed",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "files"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "path",
                  "value": "/datosnas/test-folder-renamed",
                  "description": "Virtual path del elemento a borrar"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Borra un fichero o carpeta moviéndolo a la papelera de Synology (#recycle).\n\nRequiere permiso `d` (delete) en el directorio padre.\n\nEl elemento no se elimina del disco, solo se mueve a #recycle en la raíz del mount point."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200 or error', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 400, 403, 404]);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Success response has message', function () {",
                  "  if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(body).to.have.property('message');",
                  "  }",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Files - Download",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Download Single File",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/files/download?path=/datosnas/ejemplo.stl",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "files", "download"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "path",
                  "value": "/datosnas/ejemplo.stl",
                  "description": "Virtual path del fichero a descargar"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Descarga un fichero individual con MIME type correcto y Content-Disposition.\n\nRequiere permiso `r` (read)."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200 or error', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 400, 403, 404]);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  pm.test('Has Content-Disposition header', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Disposition')).to.include('attachment');",
                  "  });",
                  "  pm.test('Has Content-Length header', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Length')).to.exist;",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Download Multiple as ZIP",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"paths\": [\n    \"/datosnas/file1.stl\",\n    \"/datosnas/file2.pdf\"\n  ]\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/files/download-zip",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "files", "download-zip"]
            },
            "description": "Descarga múltiples ficheros como un archivo ZIP.\n\nRequiere permiso `r` (read) en cada fichero.\n\nEl body debe contener un array `paths` con las rutas virtuales."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200 or error', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 400, 403, 404]);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  pm.test('Content-Type is application/zip', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type')).to.equal('application/zip');",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Files - Upload (Chunked)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Init Upload Session",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"path\": \"/datosnas/stls/model.stl\",\n  \"fileName\": \"model.stl\",\n  \"totalSize\": 50000000,\n  \"totalChunks\": 10\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/files/upload/init",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "files", "upload", "init"]
            },
            "description": "Inicia una sesión de subida chunked.\n\nRequiere permiso `w` (write) en el directorio padre del path destino.\n\nDevuelve un `uploadId` que se usa en las llamadas posteriores."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200 or error', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 400, 403, 409, 413]);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  pm.test('Response has uploadId', function () {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(body.success).to.be.true;",
                  "    pm.expect(body.uploadId).to.be.a('string');",
                  "    pm.expect(body.totalChunks).to.be.a('number');",
                  "    pm.environment.set('uploadId', body.uploadId);",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Upload Chunk",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/octet-stream"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "binary chunk data here"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/files/upload/chunk?uploadId={{uploadId}}&chunkIndex=0",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "files", "upload", "chunk"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "uploadId",
                  "value": "{{uploadId}}",
                  "description": "ID de sesión obtenido en init"
                },
                {
                  "key": "chunkIndex",
                  "value": "0",
                  "description": "Índice del chunk (0-based)"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Sube un chunk individual de datos binarios.\n\nEl body es el contenido binario crudo del chunk.\n\nSolo el usuario que inició la sesión puede subir chunks."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200 or error', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 400, 403, 404]);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  pm.test('Response confirms chunk index', function () {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(body.success).to.be.true;",
                  "    pm.expect(body.chunkIndex).to.be.a('number');",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Upload Status",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/files/upload/status?uploadId={{uploadId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "files", "upload", "status"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "uploadId",
                  "value": "{{uploadId}}",
                  "description": "ID de sesión obtenido en init"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Consulta el estado de una sesión de subida: qué chunks se han subido y cuáles faltan.\n\nÚtil para reanudar subidas interrumpidas."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200 or error', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 403, 404]);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  pm.test('Response has chunk tracking', function () {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(body.success).to.be.true;",
                  "    pm.expect(body.uploadedChunks).to.be.an('array');",
                  "    pm.expect(body.missingChunks).to.be.an('array');",
                  "    pm.expect(body.totalChunks).to.be.a('number');",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Complete Upload",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"uploadId\": \"{{uploadId}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/files/upload/complete",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "files", "upload", "complete"]
            },
            "description": "Ensambla todos los chunks en el fichero final y limpia la sesión temporal.\n\nTodos los chunks deben haberse subido previamente.\n\nDevuelve el path virtual y el tamaño final del fichero."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200 or error', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 400, 403, 404]);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  pm.test('Response has final file info', function () {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(body.success).to.be.true;",
                  "    pm.expect(body.path).to.be.a('string');",
                  "    pm.expect(body.size).to.be.a('number');",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Quota",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get User Quota",
          "request": {
